{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edecc2ca-c601-4942-92f8-9fd8792a5d19","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively integrates with Microsoft.Testing.Platform**. You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property was a bridge for .NET 9 SDK; in .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\nYou can simply remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_2bqBXH4rSD0hqVkOD36T9t","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_38349gArIfXwCqBHMdhRJv","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7aef11428b044a148819228a202883fb/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7aef11428b044a148819228a202883fb/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"dd703024-b8c2-4c1f-8346-db5da141f4b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This was a key change in .NET 10 — the new `dotnet test` integration with MTP is built-in.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform when it detects an MTP-based test project (e.g., one with `EnableMSTestRunner`).\n\n\n2. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n3. The `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still required — it marks the test project as an executable that runs on MTP.\n\nNow I'll update their project file to reflect these changes.","outputTokens":486,"requestId":"E3D9:3FC1BD:160A826:18B1056:6A0520F6"},"id":"91417f20-c634-46db-a271-2b03a7eda6fa","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:22.843Z","parentId":"bb08d5ce-9e7d-47b3-b3d7-faa8a64d1ec7"}
